## Nginx on Ubuntu
1. Add PPA repo for nginx.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/AddNginxPPA.png)
2. Detect not Found version of nginx-stable.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/404NginxStable.png)
3. Remove Not found nginx version this PPA.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/PpaPurgeNginxStable.png)
4. The NGINX PPAs are no longer used for 22.04 or 24.04. That's why I use ondrej/nginx
5. Install Nginx with ppa release.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/InstallNginxPPA.png)
6. Start Nginx.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/NginxHomePage.png)
5. Service run with command `systemctl start nginx`. In the nginx.server we can find description of behavior on the start.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/NginxServer.png)
6. Systemd run Nginx master process.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/SystemdRunMater.png)
7. Open descriptor of master process.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/OpenDescriptors.png):
- 0 - redirect stdin to /dev/null
- 1 - redirect stdout to /dev/null
- 2,3,4 - log files
All others sockets connected to the specific port
8. Reading logs `sudo tail -n 50 /var/log/nginx/access.log`.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/ReadNginxLogs.png)
9. Changed access log file path in "/etc/nginx/nginx.conf" than use `sudo systemctl reload nginx` to reload configuration.![Alt text](Lecture5/images/ChangeNginxLogPath.png)
